    "description": [
        {
            "text": "\"Linear Ionization\"  is a description of how the ionization of an atom or molecule takes place. For example, an ion with a +2 charge can be created only from an ion with a +1 charge or a +3 charge. That is, the numerical charge of an atom or molecule must change sequentially, always moving from one number to an adjacent, or sequential, number. Using sequential ionization definition.",
            "lang": "en"
        }
    ],
